** React Native vs ReactJS*

- In React Native, you don't have the usual HTML tags
	+ View => div/section/footer etc
	+ Text
	
- Style come as a tag property which receives an object with all the styles

```
export default function App() {
  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <Text>Hallo, Wir Geht's Mit Dir!</Text>
      <Text>Alles Gut?</Text>
      <Text>Ich bin keine m√ºde! :)</Text>
      <Text>ICH BIN STARK</Text>
    </View>
  );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    backgroundColor: '#7159c1',
    alignItems: 'center',
    justifyContent: 'center',
  },
});

```

- There are no style inheritance
	+ you cant put a child tag inside your style for  the mother tag
	+ you need to style every element
	+ each element behaves in a unique way



